# RetireSmart Canada

Personal Canadian retirement calculator. Client-side only. Not financial advice.

Canonical agent entry: root `AGENTS.md`. Domain math: `docs/explanation/math-model.md`. Doc system: `docs/README.md`.

## Architecture

- Types/enums in `src/types/calculator.ts` only. Prefer enums over string unions.
- `import type` under `verbatimModuleSyntax`.
- No third-party chart libs; custom SVG only.
- `localStorage` key `retiresmart_plan_v1` only — no backend.

## Math (summary — details in docs)

- Target backsolve + account buckets + RRIF rules; see `docs/explanation/math-model.md`.
- Nest-egg card = cash-aware current-path projection; →$0 band = min need; Extra Gap headline = READINESS (`solveExtraForReadiness`); BACKSOLVE @71 is design-only ([ADR 0004](../../docs/decisions/0004-extra-funding-solve.md)); Excess funded = `isFundedWithoutExtra` (§3.7–3.8). Earliest comfortable retirement = joint years earlier at active-scenario spend, same terminal ([ADR 0007](../../docs/decisions/0007-early-retirement-solve.md)). OAS = arrival year; CPP = work-start year.
- Extra/ESPP routing is symmetric: own TFSA → spouse TFSA; personal RRSP owner-only; cross-spouse RRSP spousal-only; see ADR 0006. Survivor stress defaults to primary-earner death and is identical in both engines — Plot 1/readiness/deficit must match Extra/→$0 ([ADR 0005](../../docs/decisions/0005-survivor-consistency.md), [ADR 0006](../../docs/decisions/0006-symmetric-earner-roles.md)).
- Same horizon in both engines via `resolveRetirementHorizon` (`lifeExpectancyDelta` years; default 20); readiness ↔ deficit share `analyzeRetirementShortfall`. Deprecated = `solveRequiredSavings` only — not `runProjection`.
- Do not treat all wealth as taxable RRSP; do not invent tax rules absent from that doc / ADRs.

## Testing

- Logic changes: tests in `src/test/`. Skip full runs for pure styling tweaks.
